TWO TYPES OF VARIABLERS
local and Global variable scope

Local variable is a scope which cannot work outside the function scope which is declared to.

EXAMPLE:
#include <stdio.h>

int addNumbers(int number1,int number2){
int sum = number1 + number2;
//variable sum is a local variable as it cannot be declared out of the function scope.
return sum;
}

int main() {
int result = addNumers(8,9);
printf("%d",result);
}

return 0;

Global variables are variables which are declared outside the function.

EXAMPLE:

#include <stdio.h>

int result;
//result variable is a global variable

void addNumbers("int number1,int number2){
result = number1 + number2;
printf("Result = %d",result);

int main() {

addNumbers(8,9);

return 0;
}

OUTPUT
Result = 17
